    "For governance by automated authorities to be sustainable and effective, it must achieve both sociological and normative legitimacy, ensuring that it is not only perceived as legitimate but also conforms to the values and expectations of those it governs.",
    "The emergence of Constitutional AI represents not merely an effort to develop AI systems that are safe and beneficial but also a clear bid for legitimacy.",
    "53 Sociologists have observed that nascent institutions often confront challenges of legitimation by emulating other entities in comparable positions, a phenomenon known as the heart of what makes a governing entity legitimate in the eyes of those subject to its authority.",
